The paper deals with solving a system of linear equations, which is a common problem in information theory and communication theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses computational complexity and message-passing efficiency, which are related to numerical analysis and scientific computing, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) another likely sub-category. The use of computer simulations to illustrate the properties of the proposed solver suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could also be a relevant sub-category. The iterative nature of the approach and the comparison with conventional linear-algebraic iterative solution methods suggest that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) could also be relevant sub-categories.
